message.content: cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.ET - The paper deals with the space complexity of recognizing nonregular languages, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The results involve various types of automata and their space requirements, which are also relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses some concepts from logic (cs.LO) and quantum computing (cs.ET).
